  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "Go Go Ackman 2 is an Action game, developed by Aspect and published by Banpresto, which was released in Japan in 1995. The gameplay is largely the same as the first game in the series. With the exception that Ackman can now throw enemies he picks up.\n\nGo Go Ackman was created by famous mangaka Akira Toriyama, known for his work on Dragon Ball as well as games such as Chrono Trigger and Dragon Quest.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb"
    },
    {
      "text": "Tenshi, the angel nemesis of Ackman, has enlisted the Angelic rock band Metal Angel to end Ackman. While collecting souls of his enemies, Ackman must traverse the games 5 stages to fight each band member of Metal Angel.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb_storyline"
